<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 16 at 2:31PM CDT  by NWS Jackson</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of eastern Clarke
County through 300 PM CDT...
At 231 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Crandall, or 12 miles east of Quitman, moving east at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of eastern Clarke
County.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
